record_data.filing_title: Grant County Interconnect LLC Filing of Coordination Services Agreement

record_data.record_plain_text:
COORDINATION SERVICES AGREEMENT (FOR GRANT PLAINS WIND, LLC) THIS COORDINATION SERVICES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement"), is entered into as of October 30, 2018 (the "Effective Date"), by and between Grant County Interconnect, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("GCI"), and Grant Plains Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Grant Plains", together with GCI, the "Parties" and each a "Party"). RECITALS WHEREAS, Grant Plains owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 148.2 MW (the "Grant Plains Project"); WHEREAS, Grant Wind, LLC ("Grant"), owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of approximately 151.8 MW (the "Grant Project", and jointly with the Grant Plains Project, the "Projects", and each of them individually, a "Project"); WHEREAS, Grant and Grant Plains are the sole members of GCI; WHEREAS, GCI is a party to a certain Generator Interconnection Agreement by and among itself, Southwest Power Pool, Inc. ("SPP") and Oklahoma Gas and Electric Company ("OGE"), dated December 11, 2014 (as amended, the "LGIA"), which provides for Interconnection Service (as defined in the LGIA) for the Projects, with an aggregate capacity not to exceed 300 MW; WHEREAS, Grant and Grant Plains are parties to the Amended and Restated Option and Asset Purchase Agreement dated September 8, 2015 (the "OAPA"), pursuant to which Grant Plains has the option to acquire a co-tenancy interest in the Shared Facilities, which, as used herein, has the meaning assigned to it in the OAPA, in accordance with the OAPA; WHEREAS, Grant, Grant Plains and GCI are parties to the Amended and Restated Co-Tenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement (the "Co-Tenancy Agreement"), dated as of the September 8, 2015, pursuant to which Grant and Grant Plains have agreed upon the terms governing their co-tenancy of the Shared Facilities (including the appointment of Grant as Shared Facilities Manager), and have granted GCI certain rights in respect of such Shared Facilities; WHEREAS, the rights and obligations of the Parties will commence upon Grant Plains exercise of its option in accordance with the OAPA, which is expected to occur contemporaneously with the execution of this Coordination Services Agreement; WHEREAS, Grant and GCI are parties to the Coordination Service Agreement dated September 5, 2015 establishing terms and conditions by which GCI enables Grant to receive the service from GCI that it requires to deliver its energy to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) under the LGIA (the "Grant Coordination Services Agreement", and together with the LGIA, the Co-Tenancy Agreement, and this Agreement, the "GW/GP Agreements"); and WHEREAS, Grant Plains will exercise its Option in accordance with the OAPA and, accordingly, GCI and Grant Plains are entering into this Agreement to memorialize the terms and conditions by which GCI enables Grant Plains to deliver its energy to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) under the LGIA, consistent with and as otherwise contemplated by the Grant Coordination Services Agreement. NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT 1. TERM; EARLY TERMINATION 1.1 Term: The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date first written above and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement, or (c) pursuant to Section 6.1 of this Agreement. 1.2 Early Termination: This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by either Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party, upon the earlier date that (a) Grant Plains, or its successor and assignee, shall have permanently ceased operation of the Grant Plains Project for the production of electric energy or (b) GCI assigns, transfers and conveys its rights and obligations under the LGIA to both Grant and Grant Plains in accordance with the LGIA. 2. SERVICES 2.1 Nature of Services: GCI shall provide the services hereunder to Grant Plains to enable all of the energy from the Grant Project to reach the transmission system of OGE in accordance with the LGIA (the "Coordination Service"). The Coordination Service provided by GCI to Grant Plains shall not relieve GCI of its obligations under the LGIA. The Parties also acknowledge that GCI has entered into Grant Coordination Services Agreement, including terms and conditions substantially equivalent to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. 2.2 Obligations of GCI: GCI (pursuant to its rights under the Co-Tenancy Agreement), through its managing member shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is consistent with its obligations under the LGIA and which enables the energy from Grant Plains to reach the transmission system of OGE. To the extent necessary in order to exercise the rights and perform such obligations, GCI hereby delegates its rights and obligations hereunder to Grant Plains. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, GCI (pursuant to its rights under the Co-Tenancy Agreement), through its managing member agrees to: (a) Perform its obligations under this Agreement and the LGIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the LGIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA; (b) Comply with all provisions of the LGIA to which it is subject (and all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof); (c) Promptly provide to Grant Plains any notices it receives under the LGIA from SPP or OGE, including any notices regarding emergencies under Article 13 of the LGIA; (d) Not take any steps, or omit to take any steps, without Grant Plains' written consent, to amend, assign or terminate the LGIA; and (e) Ensure that, to the maximum extent possible, any actions taken, or omitted to be taken, by Grant that may or do cause GCI to fail to comply with the LGIA, do not affect the Coordination Service received by Grant Plains hereunder. 2.3 Obligations of Grant Plains: Grant Plains shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates GCI's performance under and compliance with the LGIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Grant Plains agrees to: (a) Operate the Grant Plains Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the LGIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA; (b) Facilitate GCI's compliance with all provisions of the LGIA to which GCI is subject (and all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as it relates to the Grant Plains Project, and otherwise perform its obligations under the Co-Tenancy Agreement as necessary to cause the Shared Facilities to be maintained as agreed in the Co-Tenancy Agreement; (c) Not take any action (nor refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the LGIA by GCI; (d) Use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of the Grant Plains Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the LGIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist GCI to cure such default in accordance with the terms of the LGIA; (e) Comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by GCI, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the LGIA with respect to the Grant Plains Project; (f) Provide GCI with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the Grant Plains Project required for GCI to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the LGIA; and (g) Provide to GCI copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect GCI's performance under the LGIA. 2.4 Prior Written Consent: Except as set forth in this Agreement, neither Party shall take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Party under this Agreement, without the prior written consent of the other Party. 2.5 No Joint and Several Liability with Grant: The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject Grant Plains to joint and several liability for any actions taken by Grant that may cause noncompliance by GCI with the LGIA. 3. COST REIMBURSEMENT 3.1 Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses: Under the LGIA, GCI is responsible for certain expenses, including potential costs under Section 10.5 of the LGIA for operations and maintenance expenses. Such expenses, and those expenses incurred to administer Coordination Service to Grant and Grant Plains which are not directly caused by either Grant or Grant Plains, shall be paid for as provided in Article V of the Co-Tenancy Agreement. 4. CHANGE IN LAW 4.1 Change in Law: In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Coordination Service or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. 5. CERTAIN COVENANTS 5.1 Authority and Operational Abilities: Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. 5.2 Adverse Events: (a) If an operational issue arises at the Grant Project or Grant Plains Project that is reasonably expected to result in a breach by GCI of the LGIA or this Agreement (an "Adverse Event"), GCI shall promptly take all commercially reasonable action to resolve such issue, including curtailing the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to the Point of Interconnection (as defined in the LGIA) from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured in the reasonable judgment of GCI and Grant. (b) If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by the Grant Project or the Grant Plains Project, GCI incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind, the Project that has caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for reimbursing GCI for any such costs, expenses or penalties. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that GCI, in its reasonable discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, each Project shall be responsible for its allocable portion of the applicable costs, expenses or penalties. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for GCI, as determined in its reasonable discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, each Project will be liable for its Pro-Rata Co-Tenant Share (as defined in the Co-Tenancy Agreement) of such costs, expenses or penalties. 5.3 Priority of Curtailment: Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of curtailment pursuant to the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), unless otherwise required pursuant to the SPP market rules and administration by SPP of those rules, including with respect to curtailment and dispatch priority, the Parties agree that they shall cause the Grant and Grant Plains Projects to be curtailed as follows: (a) to the extent an OGE or SPP system emergency has occurred and OGE or SPP has specifically identified such system emergency as arising solely as a result of the Grant Project, then only the Grant Project shall be curtailed; (b) to the extent an OGE or SPP system emergency has occurred and OGE or SPP has specifically identified such system emergency as arising solely as a result of the Grant Plains Project, then only the Grant Plains Project shall be curtailed; and (c) in all other circumstances in which a curtailment occurs under the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), then both Projects shall be curtailed in the proportion of their respective Pro-Rata Co-Tenant Shares. 5.4 Notices: GCI covenants and agrees to deliver to Grant Plains: (a) Within 5 days after any manager, member, officer or director of GCI knows or has a reasonable basis to believe that any default under any of the GW/GP Agreements has occurred, a written notice of such event describing the same in detail reasonably satisfactory to Grant Plains and, together with such notice, a description of what action GCI has taken and proposes to take with respect thereto. (b) As soon as available and in any event within 25 days after the end date of each quarterly period occurring after the Effective Date, a report with respect to each of the Projects for such quarterly period, which report shall set out any curtailments pursuant to any of the GW/GP Agreements affecting energy output and the reasons for such curtailments. (c) Within 5 days after delivery or receipt thereof, a copy of each material notice, demand or other written communication in respect of any rights or obligations of any of GCI, Grant, Grant Plains, SPP and OGE (collectively, the "Grant Shared Facilities Parties") given or received by any Grant Shared Facilities Party pursuant to or relating to any of the GW/GP Agreements (including all written requests for amendments or waivers) or pursuant to or relating to any all governmental approvals necessary in connection with (i) the due execution and delivery of, and performance by each of the Parties and Grant of its obligations and the exercise of its rights under each of the GW/GP Agreements to which they are party and (ii) the legality, validity and binding effect or enforceability of the GW/GP Agreements (the "Necessary Governmental Approvals"). (d) Promptly, but in any event no later than five business days after any officer or director of GCI obtains knowledge thereof: (i) notice of any material litigation or governmental proceeding affecting GCI; (ii) notice of any event constituting a force majeure under any of the GW/GP Agreements has occurred and is continuing; and (iii) notice of any default or event which with notice or lapse of time or both would constitute a default under, or the termination, rescission or discharge (other than in accordance with its terms) of, any provision of any of the GW/GP Agreements. 5.5 Other Covenants: GCI covenants and agrees: (a) GCI shall (i) preserve and maintain its legal existence as a limited liability company in good standing in each jurisdiction in which it owns or leases property or in which the conduct of its business requires it to so qualify, as applicable, and all of its material licenses, rights, privileges and franchises necessary for the maintenance of its corporate existence, and comply, in all material respects, with its formation and governance documents and (ii) not cancel, terminate, permit the cancellation or termination of, amend, modify or change any material terms or conditions of, or grant any material consent, waiver or approval under, or take or fail to take any other action that would impair the value of its interest or impair its rights under, any of its formation and governance documents. (b) GCI shall (i) obtain and maintain, and comply in all material respects with, all Necessary Governmental Approvals as shall now or hereafter be required under applicable laws and (ii) contest any proceeding which seeks or may reasonably be expected, to rescind, terminate, modify or suspend any Necessary Governmental Approval, unless such proceeding could not be reasonably be expected to materially adversely affect GCI's ability to carry out its obligations under any of the GW/GP Agreements. (c) GCI shall not create, incur, assume or suffer to exist any Lien upon any of its property, whether now owned or hereafter acquired, except Liens for taxes which are either not yet due, are subject to a good faith contest, or otherwise bonds or reserves in an amount sufficient to repay the underlying obligation of such Lien shall have been established and remain in effect or except for such Liens that cannot be expected to materially adversely affect GCI's ability to carry out its obligations under any of the GW/GP Agreements (for purposes of this Agreement, "Lien" means, with respect to any property of any person, any mortgage, lien, deed of trust, hypothecation, fiduciary transfer of title, assignment by way of security, lien, pledge, charge, lease, sale and lease-back arrangement, easement, servitude, trust arrangement, or security interest or encumbrance of any kind in respect of such property, or any preferential arrangement having the practical effect of constituting a security interest with respect to the payment of any obligation with, or from the proceeds of, any property of any kind (and a person shall be deemed to own subject to a Lien any property that it has acquired or holds subject to the interest of a vendor or lessor under any conditional sale agreement, capital lease or other title retention agreement relating to such property)). (d) GCI shall perform its obligations under the GW/GP Agreements in accordance with prudent industry practices. (e) GCI shall at all times (a) perform and observe all of its covenants and agreements contained in any of the GW/GP Agreements and (b) promptly take any and all action as may be reasonably necessary to enforce and preserve its material rights and to collect any and all sums due to it under the GW/GP Agreements, unless, in any such case, such enforcement shall not be in the commercially reasonable interest of GCI, Grant or Grant Plains. (f) GCI shall not (i) merge or wind-up into or consolidate with any other person, or liquidate or dissolve itself (or suffer any liquidation or dissolution) or (ii) sell, lease, transfer, or otherwise dispose of its property other than ancillary services in connection with the GW/GP Agreements. (g) GCI shall not, except with the prior written approval of Grant Plains, (i) amend or modify, or consent to the amendment or modification of, any of the GW/GP Agreements or waive any material provision thereof, (ii) terminate, replace or assign any or all of its interests in any of the GW/GP Agreements or (iii) exercise any rights it may have to consent to any termination, replacement or assignment of any of the GW/GP Agreements by any party thereto or give any other material consent or exercise any material option thereunder; provided, however, that GCI shall not be required to obtain the prior written approval of Grant Plains if any action described in clauses (i) through (iii) could not reasonably be expected to (x) cause an adverse effect on Grant Plains or the Grant Plains Project or on GCI's ability to carry out its obligations under any of the GW/GP Agreements or (y) prevent Grant Plains from receiving the benefits of the LGIA. 6. MATERIAL BREACH; ASSIGNMENT UPON SURRENDER 6.1 Material Breach by Either Party: In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party's failure to cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other Party describing such breach, such non-breaching Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the breaching Party, (ii) bring an action for an injunction or to specifically enforce the provisions of this Agreement (the Parties hereby agreeing that if any Party breaches this Agreement, the injury to the other Party will be irreparable and money damages alone will not be an adequate remedy), (iii) receive amounts payable under the indemnities contained herein, (iv) subject to and solely in accordance with Article XI of the Co-Tenancy Agreement, including any additional cure periods and notice requirements set forth therein, terminate this Agreement, or (v) exercise any and all other rights and remedies not specified in this Section 6.1 which the non-defaulting Party might otherwise have at law or in equity; provided, however, that in the event of any breach by a Party of this Agreement that may give rise to a breach by any other Party pursuant to the terms of the LGIA, such non-breaching Party shall not be required to provide the breaching Party hereunder with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedy specified in clause (i) of this sentence only; and provided, further, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender of such nonbreaching Party. If a non-breaching Party (or any lender thereof) chooses to cure a breaching Party's default, the breaching Party shall reimburse such nonbreaching Party (or such Party's lender) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such non-breaching Party (or such non-breaching Party's lender) in curing such breach. 6.2 Surrender and Assignment of Shared Facilities Use Rights: Grant Plains shall have the right to assign and convey this Agreement to Grant by notice to GCI upon Grant Plains' surrender of its Shared Facilities Use Rights (as defined in the Co-Tenancy Agreement) in accordance with Section 10.2 of the Co-Tenancy Agreement. 7. FORCE MAJEURE 7.1 Force Majeure: In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party's reasonable control (each a "Force Majeure Event"), such Party shall promptly notify the other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give the other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give the other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event's expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish the other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall immediately exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event.
8. MISCELLANEOUS 8.1 Relationship of Parties: The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Except as expressly set forth in Section 2.2 with respect to GCI's delegation of its rights and obligations hereunder to Grant Plains, nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. 8.2 Non-Interference: Subject to Sections 2.2 and 2.3, each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the LGIA by any other person as permitted hereunder. 8.3 Modification and Amendment: The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties. 8.4 Waiver: The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. 8.5 Enforceability: Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of the remaining provisions hereof. 8.6 Assignment: No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of each other Party, provided, however, that Grant may (a) collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing of the Grant Project or (b) assign this Agreement to any entity in connection with a foreclosure by any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with such entity's collateral interest in this Agreement. 8.7 Indemnification: Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party's performance or nonperformance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence, willful misconduct or intentional wrongdoing by the indemnified party. However, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability; provided, however, that damages for which a Party may be liable to any other Party under another agreement will not be considered to be special, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages hereunder.
8.8 Governing Law: This Agreement shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York, without regard to its conflict of laws provisions. 8.9 Inspection of Records: Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. 8.10 Entire Agreement: This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. 8.11 Section Headings: The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. 8.12 Counterparts: This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. 8.13 Specific Performance: The Parties may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Agreement to be executed as of the Effective Date.
